The paper discusses a new approach to the delineation of thematic structures in scientific literature using clustering of citation links and local information. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), statistical learning (cs.SD), and machine learning (cs.LG).
